 Marketing team was running multiple campaigns across digital and traditional channels, targeting diverse global regions. Leadership needed a unified view of campaign effectiveness to guide budget allocation, optimize strategy, and improve ROI. However, existing reports lacked clarity, comparability, and actionable insights.







üéØ Objectives
‚Ä¢	Evaluate marketing campaign performance across regions and formats.
‚Ä¢	Identify top-performing campaigns based on Maximum ROI.
‚Ä¢	Compare spend and revenue distribution by region.
‚Ä¢	Visualize campaign type distribution (Digital vs. Traditional).
‚Ä¢	Benchmark overall ROI against target thresholds.
üõ†Ô∏è Actions Taken
‚Ä¢	Calculated and displayed key metrics: Average ROI (0.65), Total Revenue (42.54M), Total Spend (25.69M).
‚Ä¢	Used DAX logic to dynamically highlight the top campaign based on ROI.
‚Ä¢	Built comparative visuals:
o	Bar charts for spend vs. revenue by region.
o	Combo chart for spend and average ROI by campaign name.
o	Horizontal bar chart for ROI ranking.
‚Ä¢	Segmented campaign types using a pie chart.
‚Ä¢	Added a gauge chart to track total ROI against target.
üìå Key Findings
‚Ä¢	Billboards emerged as the top campaign based on maximum ROI.
‚Ä¢	Radio Ads and TV Ads showed the highest ROI percentages (~74% and ~71% respectively).
‚Ä¢	Africa and North America generated strong revenue relative to spend.
‚Ä¢	Traditional campaigns accounted for 62.5% of total campaigns, indicating a heavier investment in offline channels.
‚Ä¢	Overall ROI of 65.56% is slightly below the target of 70%, indicating near-target performance with room for optimization.


